durham , north carolina -lrb- cnn -rrb- president obama 's nomination of loretta lynch to become the country 's first african-american woman attorney general is a historic pick . her confirmation , however , is now taking on new historical relevance as her wait for a confirmation vote by the full senate drags into its sixth month .
obama nominated lynch to replace attorney general eric holder on november 8 , after holder had announced plans to leave the post weeks earlier .
senate republicans adamantly deny the delay in scheduling a vote on lynch 's nomination is because she is african-american .